TITLE: Implementing Custom Product Hooks in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Custom React hooks for managing product data state and fetching, including loading states and error handling using SWR.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/integrations/apps/tutorial/nextjs-enhance.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export function useProducts() {
    const encodedContext = useSession()?.context;
    const { data, error } = useSWR(encodedContext ? ['/api/products', encodedContext] : null, fetcher);

    return {
        summary: data,
        isLoading: !data && !error,
        isError: error,
    };
}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export function useProductList() {
    const encodedContext = useSession()?.context;
    const { data, error, mutate: mutateList } = useSWR(encodedContext ? ['/api/products/list', encodedContext] : null, fetcher);

    return {
        list: data,
        isLoading: !data && !error,
        isError: error,
        mutateList,
    };
}
```

