TITLE: Implementing Quick View Functionality with BigCommerce Product API
DESCRIPTION: This code implements a quick view feature for products. When a user clicks on a quick view button, it opens a modal and uses utils.api.product.getById to fetch the product details with a specific template for display in the modal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/stencil/utils/reference.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
$('body').on('click', '.quickview', (event) => {
    event.preventDefault();
    const productId = $(event.currentTarget).data('product-id');
    modal.open({ size: 'large' });

    utils.api.product.getById(productId, { template: 'products/quick-view' }, (err, response) => {
      modal.updateContent(response);

      modal.$content.find('.productView').addClass('productView--quickView');

      return new ProductDetails(modal.$content.find('.quickView'), context);
    });
  });
```

