TITLE: Querying Products Information for a Specific Locale in GraphQL Storefront API
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query demonstrates how to request product information for a specific locale (French) using the @shopperPreferences directive. The query retrieves the resolved locale, list of enabled locales for the channel, and localized product names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/graphql/multi-language-support.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
POST https://your_store.example.com/graphql
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

query @shopperPreferences(locale:"fr") { # specific requested locale via directive
  shopperPreferences {
    locale {
      resolved # resolved locale
    }
  }
  site {
    settings {
      locales { # list of enabled locales
        code
        isDefault
      }
    }
    products {
      edges {
        node {
          name # localized name
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

