TITLE: Sorting Products with Search Term in GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query demonstrates how to search for products using a search term ('Sample') and sort the returned products alphabetically (A_TO_Z). It returns the first two products matching the search criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/headless/products/faceted-textual-search.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
query {
  site {
    search {
      searchProducts(
        filters: {
          searchTerm: "Sample"
        }
        sort: A_TO_Z
      ) {
        products(first: 2) {
          edges {
            node {
              entityId
              name
              prices {
                price {
                  value
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

