TITLE: Injecting Template Context to JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to inject dynamic data from the template context into the client-side JavaScript code using the `inject` helper and the `jsContext` helper.  It sets the product name using `{{inject}}` and then retrieves the JSON object with `{{jsContext}}` within a `<script>` tag. This allows for dynamic data to be used in client-side logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/stencil/themes/javascript/extend.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
{{inject "myProductName" product.title}}

<script>
// Note the lack of quotes around the jsContext handlebars helper, it becomes a string automatically.
var jsContext = JSON.parse({{jsContext}}); //jsContext would output "{\"myProductName\": \"Sample Product\"}" which can feed directly into your JavaScript

console.log(jsContext.myProductName); // Will output: Sample Product
</script>
```

