TITLE: Encoding Client Secret and Verifying Webhook in Python
DESCRIPTION: This snippet encodes the client secret in base64 and sets up an HTTP function to verify incoming webhooks using the Webhook class. It handles the webhook payload and headers, attempts verification, and returns the result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/integrations/webhooks/https-webhook-overview.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
# Encode the client secret in base64
encoded_client_secret = base64.b64encode(client_secret.encode()).decode()

@functions_framework.http
def hello_http(request):
    webhook_payload = request.get_data()
    webhook_headers = request.headers
    print(str(webhook_payload))
    print(str(webhook_headers))

    result = 'no_result'

    # Use the encoded client secret
    wh = Webhook(encoded_client_secret)
    try:
        result = str(wh.verify(webhook_payload, webhook_headers))
        print('verified')
    except Exception as e:
        result = f"Could not verify: {e}"

    print(result)
    return result
```

