TITLE: Appending Footer Links with HTML and JQuery
DESCRIPTION: This HTML and JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to add custom links to the footer section via the BigCommerce control panel. It uses JQuery to dynamically append list items containing links, satisfying the WCAG 'unusual words' guideline. User-defined links should replace placeholder text for full functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/stencil/themes/accessibility/implementing-wcag-guidelines.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<script type="application/javascript" src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.2/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script>
    $(document).ready(function(){
        $("footer article[data-section-type='footer-webPages'] ul").append("<li><a href='/page-link1/'>Add Link Name1</a></li><li><a href='/page-link2/'>Add Link Name2</a></li><li><a href='/page-link3/'>Add Link Name3</a></li>")
    });
</script>
```

