TITLE: GraphQL Query with Depth of 11
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query illustrates a query with a depth of 11, demonstrating how nested objects contribute to the overall query depth.  Each level of nesting increases the depth, which, if exceeding the limit of 16, will result in an error.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/graphql/index.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
query {                                 // depth 0
  site {                                // depth 1
    products {                          // depth 2
      edges {                           // depth 3
        node {                          // depth 4
          entityId                      // depth 5
          variants {                    // depth 5
            edges {                     // depth 6
              node {                    // depth 7
                entityId                // depth 8
                options {               // depth 8
                  edges {               // depth 9
                    node {              // depth 10
                      entityId          // depth 11
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

