TITLE: GraphQL Query with Filter and Character Limit
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query demonstrates the use of filters and character limits, which do not contribute to query complexity in the BigCommerce API. The query filters blog posts by tags and limits the character length of the plain text summary, showing that these features do not increase complexity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/graphql/index.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
query {
  site {
    content {
      blog {
        posts (filters: {tags:["Most Popular"]}) { // Filter argument
          edges {
            node {
              plainTextSummary (characterLimit: 100) // Character limit
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

