TITLE: Fetching Variant Inventory with GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: GraphQL query to retrieve inventory levels for product variants, filtered by product entity ID. Returns variant details including SKU and stock levels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bigcommerce/docs/blob/main/docs/storefront/graphql/inventory/queries.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
query {
  site {
    products (entityIds:[113]) {
      edges {
        node {
          entityId
          name
          variants {
            edges {
              node {
                entityId
                sku
                inventory {
                  aggregated {        // By default, includes inventory from only the default location 
                    availableToSell
                    warningLevel
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

